org.nerd4j.csv.reader

Interface CSVReader<M>

  • Type Parameters:
    M - type of the data model representing the CSV record.
    All Superinterfaces:
    AutoCloseable, Closeable

    public interface CSVReader<M>
extends Closeable
    Represents a CSV data source reader.

    Reads a record in the CSV source and creates an object of type M that represents such record.

    Synchronization

    CSV readers are not synchronized. It is recommended to create separate CSV reader instances for each thread. If multiple threads access a CSV reader concurrently, it must be synchronized externally.

    Author:
    Nerd4J Team

      • readModel

        M readModel()
     throws IOException,
            CSVToModelBindingException,
            CSVProcessException
        Reads a record in the CSV source and returns the corresponding data model.

        This method has a cleaner interface but handles processing errors by throwing CSVProcessException therefore it may be slow. If performance matters use read() instead.

        Returns:
        the outcome of the reading process.
        Throws:
        IOException - if an error occurs reading the CSV source.
        CSVToModelBindingException - if an error occurs during model binding.
        CSVProcessException - if an error occurs during data processing.

      • read

        CSVReadOutcome<M> read()
                throws IOException,
                       CSVToModelBindingException
        Reads a record in the CSV source and returns a CSVReadOutcome containing the read data and the read execution context.

        IMPORTANT for performance reasons there is only one instance of the read outcome. So the internal values of this object may vary during execution.

        Returns:
        the outcome of the reading process.
        Throws:
        IOException - if an error occurs reading the CSV source.
        CSVToModelBindingException - if an error occurs during model binding.
